#234935 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#234935 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bdruzzilro86846.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kas>Kas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(7/17/01 1:32:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> In the beginning of my days, I played a human cleric. <br>
<br>
One day, while roaming about in EC, my little cleric of about 12 levels was assaulted by a wandering mummy. I ran as fast as I could, but it seemed I would not be able to outrun this thing.<br>
<br>
Suddenly, I was spammed with battle messages. I stopped to see what was happening, and there stood Xantess, finishing off my persuer. It was so fast, I had never seen damage done like that before. I was utterly amazed.<br>
<br>
We chatted for a bit, and I asked her a few questions about her monk. I found myself not only impressed with the ability of the monk, but the attitude of the person behind it as well.<br>
<br>
That night, Kastian was born. <br>
<br>
Over the next few months, I saw Xantess here and there, usually dueling some poor fool in the EC tunnel. I recall when Kas was level 15, Xantess offered 50pp to any lowbie who could do 50 points of damage to her in a duel. I accepted this challenge, (a sort of 'student fights master' scenario i guess) and promptly was running from by nearby bind point. I think I had done about 30 points, and Xan had been easy on me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
These kinds of things happened now and then during my own journey up the level ladder. I knew I'd probably never be quite like her, no matter what level I attained. She would always offer advice when asked, and even offered to help me personally in several situations. (difficult camps, etc.) Looking back now, it is a shame I didn't take her up on those offers. I'd always enjoyed her company.<br>
<br>
When her account was hacked, I offered my services, though I knew there was little I could do to help her get back on her feet. A month later, I saw her again, better equipped than I, and as always in good spirits. It appeared she didn't need too much help. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The last time I saw Xantess, we fought on the rooftop 'mini arena' in North Freeport. She would beat me down near death (even using some terrible dps weapons she was carrying around for fun), then bind me up again, and continue. We talked as we fought, and she told me about the Ranger BotB spectacle. I wish I had been there to see it, perhaps more than anything Ive seen in EQ. After a while, I managed to disarm her, and was instantly sorry, as she began to trounce me with her epic fists. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In the last few months, I've often wondered what had become of her. It is good to finally know.<br>
<br>
Xantess, thank you for being a friend. I wish you the best in whatever you do. <br>
<br>
/hug Xantess<br>
<br>
Kastian Taceo<br>
